Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and bilirubinuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting significant renal dysfunction, possibly acute or chronic kidney disease with impaired concentrating ability. The low HbA1c with normal serum glucose and high urine glucose/ketones may indicate recent onset or fluctuating hyperglycemia. Further nephrological and diabetic evaluation is recommended. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Prompt clinical correlation and follow-up are advised.
